In thi s approach the client speciÔ¨Åes the version number as a query parameter i n the request, as follows: http://www.foo.com/customers?version=v2 Th e server may choose to honor the query parameter or even ignore it.
A simple example of this might look like http://v1.example.com/service/ or http://api.exam ple.com/service/v1/.
The representation of an API is immutable, and a fresh URI spa ce needs to be created, such as, http://api.example.com/service/v2/,w ith the publication of a new version.
So in API versioning, it makes sense to introduce the version information in the URL a s follows: http://www.foo.com/v1/customers In this URL, v1 deÔ¨Ånes th e major version identiÔ¨Åer.
